executor_description: ​To book an appointment for a customer for a desired service.

value.description: The unique id of the service for which the appointment is booked. Source: Can be retrieved using the Fetch Services API, by querying with the service name.
The unique id of the staff associated with the service. Source: Can be fetched from Fetch Staffs API based on staff name.
The unique id of the resource associated with the service.

The starting time from which the appointment needs to be booked. (24-hour time format)
format: dd-MMM-yyyy HH:mm:ss (e.g. 30-Apr-2019 22:00:00)

End time till which the resource has to be booked. Applicable only for resource booking service.(24-hour time)
format: dd-MMM-yyyy HH:mm:ss (e.g. 30-Apr-2019 22:00:00)
The timezone under which the appointment needs to be booked.

The details of the customer which needs to be recorded for booking the appointment. They are the customer's name, email address and contact number. They must be represented as a JSON like below.

e.g. {"name":"John", "email":"john@email.com", "phone_number":"9876543201"}
Additional information about the appointment.

The amount a user has paid for the booking.
e.g.{"cost_paid":"100.00"}

executor_description: To fetch a list of appointments from a specified start date to an end date. Can also filter based on staff or service or status.

value.description: The unique ID of the staff for whom the appointments need to be fetched.
The unique ID of the service for which the appointments need to be fetched.

Start date and time from when the appointments have to be fetched
format: dd-MMM-yyyy HH:mm:ss (e.g. 30-Apr-2019 22:00:00)

End date and time until when the appointments have to be fetched
format: dd-MMM-yyyy HH:mm:ss (e.g. 30-Apr-2019 22:00:00)
Status of the appointment. It can have any one of the following values: UPCOMING, CANCEL, ONGOING, PENDING, COMPLETED, NO_SHOW, PENDING_PAYMENT, PAYMENT_FAILURE.

If true, fetches custom fields.
values: true, false
Denotes name of the customer. Fetches appointments that contains this particular customer's name.
Denotes email address of the customer. Fetches appointments that contains this particular customer's email address.

Denotes contact number of the customer. Fetches appointments that contains this particular customer's phone number.
Note: All the above customer parameters are fetched based on 'contains' logic and not 'equal to' logic. That is, they are searched if the passed value is present, rather than requiring an exact match.

executor_description: To add staff to your Zoho Bookings account. This can be done by the admin and Super admin.

subType.description: The email id of the staff
The role of the staff. It can take any of the these values - Admin, Manager, Staff.
The date of birth of the staff  format: dd-MMM-yyyy HH:mm:ss (e.g. 30-Apr-2019 22:00:00)  (or)  dd-MMM-yyyy hh:mm:ss (e.g. 30-Apr-2019 10:00:00 PM)
The additional information about the staff
The phone number of the staff
The services that the staff has been assigned to. You can send a single service or a list of services in the below format.  ["service_id"] (OR) ["service_id_1", service_id_2"]

queryParams.description: The unique id of the staff which must be fetched. value: {{staff_id}}
The unique id if the service which must be fetched. value: {{service_id}}

queryAttributes.description: The unique id of the staff which must be fetched.
The unique id if the service which must be fetched.

Unique email address of the staff whose details must be fetched. 
Note: This parameter is fetched based on 'contains' logic and not 'equal to' logic. That is, staff emails are searched if the passed value is present rather than requiring an exact match.
